<text matrix="1 0 0 1 -122.113 39.6472" transformations="translations" pos="151.211 566.956" stroke="kn_grau" type="minipage" width="647.043" height="34.1" depth="6.71" valign="top" size="footnote">Here are some practice objects:</text>
<text matrix="1 0 0 1 0 431.362" pin="h" transformations="translations" pos="0 42.278" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="1680" height="75.2125" depth="47.85" valign="top" style="item">You&apos;ll notice one object of a selected group (last selected) has a different outline. This is the \ul{reference object} for aligning etc.</text>
<text matrix="1 0 0 1 -128.885 17.4162" transformations="translations" pos="251.22 102.469" stroke="kn_grau" type="minipage" width="814.222" height="34.441" depth="6.985" valign="top" size="footnote">Try selecting the red vertex in this graph:</text>
